## 3. Phase 0 – Server Grundsetup (Tag 1–2)

### 3.1 Erster Login & User anlegen

```bash
ssh -i ~/.ssh/hetzner_vps root@DEINE_VPS_IP

adduser deploy
usermod -aG sudo deploy

mkdir -p /home/deploy/.ssh
cp /root/.ssh/authorized_keys /home/deploy/.ssh/
chown -R deploy:deploy /home/deploy/.ssh
chmod 700 /home/deploy/.ssh && chmod 600 /home/deploy/.ssh/authorized_keys
```

### 3.2 SSH absichern

```bash
nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
# PermitRootLogin no
# PasswordAuthentication no
# PubkeyAuthentication yes

systemctl restart sshd
```

### 3.3 Lokale SSH-Config

```
# ~/.ssh/config
Host vps
  HostName DEINE_VPS_IP
  User deploy
  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/hetzner_vps
```

Ab jetzt reicht: `ssh vps`

### 3.4 Firewall

```bash
sudo apt install ufw -y
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing
sudo ufw allow 22/tcp
sudo ufw allow 80/tcp
sudo ufw allow 443/tcp
sudo ufw enable
```

### 3.5 Software installieren

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y curl git unzip build-essential fail2ban

# Node.js (via nvm)
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
source ~/.bashrc
nvm install --lts && nvm use --lts

# PM2
npm install -g pm2
pm2 startup

# PostgreSQL 16
sudo apt install -y postgresql-16 postgresql-contrib

# PgBouncer
sudo apt install -y pgbouncer

# Caddy
sudo apt install -y debian-keyring debian-archive-keyring apt-transport-https
curl -1sLf 'https://dl.cloudsmith.io/public/caddy/stable/gpg.key' | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/caddy-stable-archive-keyring.gpg
curl -1sLf 'https://dl.cloudsmith.io/public/caddy/stable/debian.deb.txt' | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/caddy-stable.list
sudo apt update && sudo apt install caddy

# rclone
curl https://rclone.org/install.sh | sudo bash

# Unattended Security Updates
sudo apt install -y unattended-upgrades
sudo dpkg-reconfigure --priority=low unattended-upgrades
```

### 3.6 Fail2ban

```bash
sudo systemctl enable fail2ban
sudo systemctl start fail2ban
```

