## 6. Phase 3 – Cron Jobs intern (Woche 3–4)

**Vorher:** 21 Jobs auf cron-jobs.org → HTTP-Call auf Vercel → 30s Limit

**Nachher:** 21 Jobs als node-cron intern im Backend → kein Limit, kein externer Aufruf

### 6.1 Alle 21 Jobs nach Zeitplan

| Job                      | Intervall   | DB-Queries |
|--------------------------|-------------|------------|
| translate                | 5 Min       | ~3–5       |
| dsgvo-export             | 10 Min      | ~10–15     |
| process-failed-emails    | 2 Std       | 3          |
| check-service-limits     | 6 Std       | ~12        |
| auto-complete-bookings   | 6 Std       | 2          |
| booking-reminders        | täglich     | 5          |
| check-connect-deadline   | täglich     | 2          |
| check-provider-approvals | täglich     | 2          |
| cleanup-old-records      | täglich     | 6          |
| daily-report             | täglich     | 7          |
| keep-company-alive       | –           | 2          |
| platform-stats           | –           | 5          |
| system-monitor           | –           | 8          |
| health-check             | –           | ~5         |
| notification-nudges      | –           | 4          |
| check-temp-plan-expiry   | –           | ~4         |
| monthly-financial        | monatlich   | 4          |
| monthly-report           | monatlich   | 9          |
| weekly-limit-report      | Mo 7:00     | 4          |
| yearly-tax-export        | 1. Jan      | ~8         |
| installments             | –           | NO-OP      |

### 6.2 Cleanup in bestehenden Job integrieren

```typescript
// In cleanup-old-records Job:

// Abgelaufene Refresh Tokens (>1 Tag über Ablauf)
await db.none(`
  DELETE FROM refresh_tokens
  WHERE expires_at < NOW() - INTERVAL '1 day'
`);

// Benutzte / abgelaufene Password Resets
await db.none(`
  DELETE FROM password_resets
  WHERE expires_at < NOW() OR used_at IS NOT NULL
`);

// Alte gelesene Notifications (> 90 Tage)
await db.none(`
  DELETE FROM notifications
  WHERE read = TRUE AND created_at < NOW() - INTERVAL '90 days'
`);
```

### 6.3 Cron Scheduler

```typescript
// src/crons/index.ts
import cron from 'node-cron';
import { runTranslate } from './jobs/translate';
import { runDsgvoExport } from './jobs/dsgvo-export';

export function startCronJobs() {
  cron.schedule('*/5 * * * *', async () => {
    await runTranslate().catch(err => console.error('[cron:translate]', err));
  });

  cron.schedule('*/10 * * * *', async () => {
    await runDsgvoExport().catch(err => console.error('[cron:dsgvo-export]', err));
  });

  cron.schedule('0 8 * * *', async () => {
    await runBookingReminders().catch(err => console.error('[cron:booking-reminders]', err));
  });

  console.log('[cron] Alle Jobs gestartet');
}
```

