## 14. S4 – GitHub Runners & Automatisierte Tests

### Stufe 1 – Basis CI (sofort, 30 Min Aufwand)

```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yml
name: CI
on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  pull_request:

jobs:
  quality:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with: { node-version: '22', cache: 'npm' }
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npm run type-check
      - run: npm run lint
      - run: npm run build
```

### Stufe 2 – Playwright E2E (nach erster stabiler Version)

**Kritische Flows:**
- Register → E-Mail verify → Login
- Login → Refresh Token → weiter surfen
- Passwort vergessen → Reset → neues Passwort → Login
- Buchung erstellen (kompletter Flow)
- Provider-Profil anlegen

### Stufe 3 – Self-hosted Runner auf VPS

```bash
mkdir /home/deploy/actions-runner && cd /home/deploy/actions-runner
curl -o actions-runner.tar.gz -L \
  https://github.com/actions/runner/releases/latest/download/actions-runner-linux-x64-latest.tar.gz
tar xzf actions-runner.tar.gz
./config.sh --url https://github.com/DEIN-USER/DEIN-REPO --token TOKEN
./svc.sh install && ./svc.sh start
```

